<br />False,  Blargg's tests will fail if the IRQ is fired ONE CPU cycle off from where it belongs.  So you can have right scanline but wrong split second (CPU cycle).  It sounds like your IRQ may only be firing at the wrong time in relation to M2 which I discussed above a few posts back.  This is easy todo if you handle your enabling/disabling improperly.</div>

